CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 27, 1958, pg. 28, reads: "Marching Dolls - Pretty girls and marching bands were very much in evidence on Downtown streets Monday afternoon as thousands of Pittsburghers turned out for the parade honoring the Pittsburgh Pirates... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Marching band in parade honoring Pittsburgh Pirates, in front of People's First National Bank, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
